litter /ˈlɪtə/

(littering,littered,litters) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Litter is rubbish or waste that is left lying around outside. 垃圾 

例： If you see litter in the corridor, pick it up. 如果你看到走廊里有垃圾，就把它捡起来。 

2. V-T If a number of things litter a place, they are scattered around it or over it. 散放在 

例： Glass from broken bottles litters the sidewalk. 碎瓶子的玻璃渣散落在人行道上。 

3. littered ADJ 散放的 [v-link ADJ prep] 

例： The entrance hall is littered with toys. 入口大厅里散落着玩具。 

4. ADJ If something is littered with things, it contains many examples of it. 充满的 [v-link ADJ 'with' n] 

例： History is littered with men and women spurred into achievement by a father's disregard. 历史上常有受父亲漠视的刺激而取得成就的男男女女。 

5. N-COUNT A litter is a group of animals born to the same mother at the same time. 一窝 

例： ...a litter of pups. …一窝小狗。

